FAQs
What are the basic requirements to study at Tbilisi State Medical University?
The basic requirements include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, language proficiency in English, and passing the entrance exam specific to the university.

Is studying at TSMU expensive?
Tuition fees and living expenses at TSMU are relatively affordable compared to Western Europe and North America. Scholarships and financial aid can also help reduce costs.

How can I apply for scholarships to study at TSMU?
You can apply for scholarships through the university, as well as through Georgian government programs and private organizations. Qadri-International can assist you in finding and applying for suitable scholarships.

Are degrees from TSMU recognized worldwide?
Yes, degrees from TSMU are widely recognized and respected globally. Graduates often have the qualifications needed to practice medicine in various countries around the world.

What support can Qadri-International provide for prospective medical students?
Qadri-International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, visa processing, and pre-departure guidance, ensuring a smooth and successful journey to studying abroad.
